[Student "S"]
[Deal "W:A64.KJ9.AKQJ9.KQ T82.7542.64.A632 J3.AQT86.T3.JT74 KQ975.3.8752.985"]
[Auction "W"]
2C pass 2H pass 4NT pass 5D pass 6H pass pass pass
[Result ""]
{EAST makes a positive 3

♥

response to WEST's 2♣ opener.

This promises at least 8 points and a 5-card suit with two or more honors.

WEST only needs to know one thing - how many Aces in the EAST hand.

A Blackwood 4NT tells her the answer is one, so she bids 6

♥

.}
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 2, chOption: E, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 0, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
{Baker Bidpractice/Set7 3}
[Dealer "S"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "6NT"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Student "S"]
[Deal "S:A97.QJ42.KQ86.A5 J832.T73.J932.64 KQ.K6.A4.KQJ9732 T654.A985.T75.T8"]
[Auction "S"]
1NT pass 4C pass 4S pass 6NT pass pass pass
[Result ""]
{When SOUTH opens 1NT, point-count alone tells NORTH that 6NT can surely be made.

SOUTH is bound to hold at least two Aces. But NORTH doesn't want to miss a Grand slam.

NORTH bids 4♣, (Gerber), and SOUTH admits to just two Aces.

So NORTH settles for the small slam.}
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: S, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 0, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
